				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, Corpse Spamming is not an advantage. If you leave even one item on the corpse, then the corpse isn't an empty corpse.<BR>
<BR>
Why litter several corpses on the ground? Some folks do it just out of general mayhem. They think its funny so they do it. Others are a bit more evil.<BR>
<BR>
See, when the area with all the corpses becomes &quot;visible&quot; (i.e. within range of clipping plane, regardless of whether or not you can actually see it), it causes a big load. Your computer has to load all those extra graphics. This can cause people to go linkdead if their vid cards can barely handle EQ in the first place.<BR>
<BR>
Ahhh, but it gets even worse. Once in awhile, someone figures out how to corpse spam in such a way that anyone who actually views the mess will not only go LD but will not be able to log back in without locking up or going LD again. Only two races of characters can cause this to happen, so fortunately, it doesn't happen too frequently.<BR>
<BR>
The ability to exploit this bug and cause problems has been greatly reduced in the last several months but it is still around. If you ever see certain zones like West FP (bug is easiest to create there) being brought down for a short period, it may be because of this bug.<BR>
<BR>
While this fix won't stop the problem it will help to limit it somewhat. Og, and btw... Guides and GMs don't like corpse spammers much, so I wouldn't advise being a corpse spammer.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
