	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Actually, it IS an advantage to some people - especially melee's who can't bind just anywhere.<BR>
<BR>
Let's say I'm bound in Shadowhaven, but I'm going on a Fear raid.  Most raids like the melee to bind in the tunnel zoneline to Ogguk.  Well, damn...I really don't want to give up my Shadowhaven bind.  So, I have a guard kill me, or a real quick duel with someone - away from Guards.  I then loot everything off my corpse (except one measley item).<BR>
<BR>
Now, I have a corpse relatively near the Soulbinder in SH.  So, I run off to my Fear raid...getting bound in tunnel to Ogguk.<BR>
<BR>
Fear raid ends.  I send a /gu to one of my guild clerics/paladins that happen to be in SH and have them rez me.  Free port back to SH and the Soulbinder.<BR>
<BR>
That's just one, and not a very good one, example of why people leave corpses.  Personally, I disagree with it.  I think it's an exploit and I'm glad they are doing something about it...even if it's not very strict.
				</font>
			</td>

